<%= render_partial("about/fork_me.html.erb") %>

<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="span12 row-fluid">
    <h1> use <b><a href="/datasets">snorkel</a> </b>
    and stop data <b>mishaps</b>
    </h1>

  </div>

  <div class="row-fluid">
    <div class="clearfix">
      <div class="pull-left" style="margin: auto; text-align: center">
          <img src="/images/no-diving.png"> </img>
          <img src="/images/yes-snorkeling.png"> </img>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="clearfix mbl mtl">
      <a style="zoom: 2" class="btn btn-success" href="<%= url_for('about.index') %>">take the tour</a>
    </div>
    <div class="span4">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <div>
          <p>
            <b>snorkel</b> is a time based data analysis UI that is
            <b>complementary</b> to your monitoring software. After you spot an
            anomaly in a time series graph, snorkel helps you create, refine
            and compare queries on your data that explain <b>why</b> your
            graphs are changing.  </p> 
      </div>
      <h2>Example Uses</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>monitor push and deployment health</li>
        <li>track and diagnose client errors</li>
        <li>diagnose performance regressions</li>
        <li>locate optimization opportunities</li>
        <li>analyze performance experiments</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="span1"></div>
    <div class="span4">
      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Realtime drilldowns</li>
        <li>Powerful comparison queries</li>
        <li><a href="http://github.com/logv/snorkel/wiki/Backends">Supports mongo or postgres</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://github.com/logv/grafana-snorkel-datasource" target="_blank">
          Dashboarding with Grafana</a></li>
        <li><s>100%</s>85% uncommented Node.JS</li>
        <li>(mostly) Mobile friendly UI</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Drawbacks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No JOIN operations</li>
        <li>Snorkel won't fix the problems it finds</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>
